during M2 compared with {\$} 2 during M1. The proton plasma pressure accounts for only a fraction (24{\%} for M1 and 64{\%} for M2) of the drop in magnetic pressure upon entry into the dayside boundary layer. This result suggests that heavy ions of planetary origin, not considered in this analysis, may provide the ''missing'' pressure. If these planetary ions were hot due to ''pickup'' in the magnetosheath, the required density for pressure balance would be an ion density of {\$} 1 cm {\`{A}} 3 for an ion temperature of {\$} 10 8 K.},
